node.text:
The epic ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ journey continues as Dogfish Head founders Sam & Mariah make their way up the eastern seaboard! In this episode, watch as Sam & Mariah uncover the importance of land and water conservation at both Bristol Marsh Preserve and Cove Mountain Preserve. They also take a trip to Staten Island, NY to see how @nature_org is working to benefit communities impacted by Hurricane Sandy. To learn more about ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ and our work with TNC, head to dogfish.com/mothernature (link in bio)! 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis

*Dogfish Head is a proud supporter of The Nature Conservancy (TNC) and its mission to conserve the lands & waters on which all life depends’ (www.nature.org). TNC does not endorse any specific product, including all those visible in the road trip docuseries. Purchase of Dogfish Head products will not result in a contribution to TNC. Learn more at www.dogfish.com/TNC.

node.text:
We’ve set out on an epic journey to learn more about the environmental issues facing us globally and on a localized level, and we’ve enlisted the help of our longtime partners @nature_org. In this episode of our ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ journey, Sam & Mariah take a deep dive into the history behind Bear Island/Potomac Gorge (@nature_dcmdva) and the significance of TNC’s oyster aquaculture and restoration work amidst the pandemic. They also get a close-up look at how TNC is bringing nature’s benefits to urban residents in Wilmington, Delaware (@nature_delaware). So, settle in and let’s do this! To learn more about ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ and our work with TNC, head to dogfish.com/mothernature! 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis

node.text:
It’s been months in the making … an epic road trip from Florida to Maine with one very clear mission: learn more about the environmental issues facing us globally and on a localized level. And who better to help us along our ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ journey than our longtime partners @nature_org (TNC). In a four-part docuseries, watch as Dogfish Head founders Sam & Mariah stop at 13 distinct sites to tackle issues like oyster aquaculture and restoration, land and water conservation, and so much more. In this episode, Sam & Mariah get their feet wet (literally!) with visits to Blowing Rocks Preserve @natureflorida, Goldbug Island Living Shoreline in South Carolina and the Black River Preserve @tnc_nc. To learn more about ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ and our work with TNC, head to dogfish.com/mothernature! 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis

*Dogfish Head is a proud supporter of The Nature Conservancy (TNC) and its mission to conserve the lands & waters on which all life depends’ (www.nature.org). TNC does not endorse any specific product, including all those visible in the road trip docuseries. Purchase of Dogfish Head products will not result in a contribution to TNC. Learn more at www.dogfish.com/TNC.

node.text: At Dogfish Head, we rely on the goodness of Mother Nature to provide us with the beautiful and bountiful culinary ingredients used in our off-centered beverages and dishes. And with a restless desire to explore at the heart of everything we do, Dogfish Head founders Sam & Mariah Calagione were eager to learn more about the environmental issues facing us globally and on a localized level. So, they packed up and hit the road for a month-long journey in our backyard that is the eastern seaboard. From oyster reefs to the very first @nature_org preserve, we’ve captured it all. Follow along over the coming weeks as we unpack and reflect on an incredible journey. 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis #conserveandprotect

Bursting with invigorating flavors of bright-citrusy lemon, slightly sweet berries and just a bit of salt, Lemon Quest is the perfect pairing for your next adventure! And because of its wholesome, all-natural ingredients and its connection to @nature_org (TNC), we’ve lovingly nicknamed Lemon Quest, “the brew that gives back.” As a proud supporter of TNC, we’ve donated more than $50K to TNC to celebrate the launch of this tasty non-alcoholic wheat brew, and you’ll find their logo on every package of Lemon Quest to showcase the awesome collaborative work we’ve been doing to bring our ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ journey to life. To learn more about #MotherNatureLetsDoThis and our work with TNC, head to dogfish.com/mothernature (link in bio)! 🍋🍺🌱

We’ve set out on an epic journey to learn more about the environmental issues facing us globally and on a localized level, and we’ve enlisted the help of our longtime partners @nature_org. In this episode of our ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ journey, Sam & Mariah take a deep dive into the history behind Bear Island/Potomac Gorge (@nature_dcmdva) and the significance of TNC’s oyster aquaculture and restoration work amidst the pandemic. They also get a close-up look at how TNC is bringing nature’s benefits to urban residents in Wilmington, Delaware (@nature_delaware). So, settle in and let’s do this! To learn more about ‘Mother Nature, Let’s Do This!’ and our work with TNC, head to dogfish.com/mothernature! 🌱 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis

*Dogfish Head is a proud supporter of The Nature Conservancy (TNC) and its mission to conserve the lands & waters on which all life depends’ (www.nature.org). TNC does not endorse any specific product, including all those visible in the road trip docuseries. Purchase of Dogfish Head products will not result in a contribution to TNC. Learn more at www.dogfish.com/TNC.

node.text: A beanie in the middle of summer may seem crazy, but when it calls to Mother Nature … is it really?! All this month we’re featuring snippets from Dogfish Head founders Sam & Mariah’s month-long ‘Mother Nature, Let’s  Do This!’ road trip, so it’s only fitting that this is the month to snag your ‘On the Road’ badge at dogfish.com/shop. Tack it to this very beanie, sew it on your backpack, or let it fly on your sweet jean jacket … whatever or wherever, just make sure you’re enjoying the splendor of the great outdoors! 🏕 #MotherNatureLetsDoThis #offcentered

node.text: I scream … you scream … we ALL scream for Hazy-O! ice cream! Yep … we’ve taken our Hazy-O! hazy IPA and turned it into a first-of-its-kind, oat milk-based dessert! Created in partnership with @tipsyscoop, this dairy-free offering is an all-new ice cream innovation made with the same oat milk found in Hazy-O!, and packed with notes of chocolate, caramel, cinnamon and coconut. And, what it lacks in lactose it makes up for in silky smoothness! To learn more about this sweet new treat (including how to snag a pint!), hop on over to dogfish.com (link in bio)! 🍦🍺🎯 #offcentered #HazyO #tipsyscoop
